Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper deals with the problem of line spectrum estimation, which is a common problem in signal processing. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper formulates a semidefinite program to recover the continuous-valued frequencies, which involves optimization and information theory concepts. 
- cs.SP (Speech Processing): The techniques proposed in the paper can be applied to speech signals, which often have line spectra. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method to take advantage of known structures of frequency blocks, which can be seen as a form of structured learning. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper presents numerical experiments to show the performance of the proposed method, which involves numerical analysis techniques.
